{"id": "duc04-testb-2:5#15", "contents": "The senior Olympic official, Marc Hodler, who made stunning allegations of corruption within the IOC, revealed on Sunday that he had been \"muzzled\" by IOC President Juan Antonio Samaranch. Hodler, a Swiss member of the IOC executive board, stated that Samaranch had instructed him to remain silent on the matter. This directive came in the form of an order not to attend a scheduled routine news conference. Hodler's allegations of corruption have sent shockwaves through the organization, and it appears that Samaranch is attempting to contain the fallout."}
